<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-12-28T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-12-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/2083: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sheffield</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-12-28T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 28,
                                        1926—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>377. I concur in conclusions set forth in last paragraph of your 522,
                            December 27, 2 p.m. Department has just received a copy of telegram sent
                            last evening to President Calles and Señor Morones by Petroleum
                            Companies in New York,<note n="62" xml:id="d388fn62"><hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> suggesting extension of time. Please keep
                            Department closely informed by telegraph of all developments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>